    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c8b73637_c8dacedd",
        "filename": "luci_notify/api/config/notify.proto",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 116,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000325
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-03-27T01:42:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I thought config files had multiline support, but they do not.\n  https://github.com/luci/luci-go/blob/master/common/proto/multiline_test.go\n\nAfter reading the template docs, I think we have to define subject and body definitions independently, partly because one uses text/template, and the other html/template.\n\nThe templating library has support for parsing all template files in a directory, which would make them all available in the same namespace and be able to include from each other, but the file names become the template names.\n\nWhat about:\n\nluci-notify/\n  email-templates/\n    subject/\n      foo\n    body/\n      foo\n\nAlternatively, it could be:\n\nluci-notify/\n  email-templates/\n    foo-subject\n    foo-body\n\nBut the names of the templates would have to be \"foo-subject\" and \"foo-body\" whenever it was explicitly defined. The subject/body name spaces would still be independent, which leads me towards two different directories.\n\nThe files can define additional template names internally, if people want to get fancy.",
      "parentUuid": "76739c86_363fd5a1",
      "revId": "d2b6ed8db1683f6656c75d7881e926bcca338f73",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    }
